<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:212px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Hpb.jpg" class="image" title="Helena Blavatsky, co-founder of the Theosophical Society"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Hpb.jpg/210px-Hpb.jpg" width="210" height="312" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Hpb.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Helena Blavatsky, co-founder of the <a href="/wiki/Theosophical_Society" title="Theosophical Society">Theosophical Society</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Elena Petrovna Gan</b> (<a href="/wiki/Russian_language" title="Russian language">Russian</a>: <span lang="ru" xml:lang="ru">Елена Петровна Ган</span>, also Hélène, 12 August <small>[<a href="/wiki/Old_Style_and_New_Style_dates" title="Old Style and New Style dates">O.S.</a> 31 July]</small> 1831, <a href="/wiki/Dnipropetrovsk" title="Dnipropetrovsk">Yekaterinoslav</a>, <a href="/wiki/Yekaterinoslav_Governorate" title="Yekaterinoslav Governorate">Yekaterinoslav</a>, <a href="/wiki/Russian_Empire" title="Russian Empire">Russian Empire</a> (today <a href="/wiki/Dnipropetrovsk" title="Dnipropetrovsk">Dnipropetrovsk</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ukraine" title="Ukraine">Ukraine</a>) – May 8, 1891, <a href="/wiki/London" title="London">London</a>), better known as <b>Helena Blavatsky</b> (<a href="/wiki/Russian_language" title="Russian language">Russian</a>: <span lang="ru" xml:lang="ru">Елена Блаватская</span>) or <b>Madame Blavatsky</b>, born <b>Helena von Hahn</b>, was a founder of <a href="/wiki/Theosophy" title="Theosophy">Theosophy</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Theosophical_Society" title="Theosophical Society">Theosophical Society</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
