<li><i>"Madame Blavastky, Medium and Magician"</i>, <a href="/wiki/John_Symonds" title="John Symonds">John Symonds</a>, Odhams, 1959.</li>
<li><i>"Madame Blavatsky: The Woman Behind the Myth"</i> by <a href="/wiki/Marion_Meade" title="Marion Meade">Marion Meade</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0399123768" class="internal">ISBN 0399123768</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.theosociety.org/pasadena/hpb-tm/hpbtm-hp.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.theosociety.org/pasadena/hpb-tm/hpbtm-hp.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>H. P. Blavatsky and the Theosophical Movement</i></a> by <a href="/wiki/Charles_Ryan" title="Charles Ryan">Charles Ryan</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0911500804" class="internal">ISBN 0-911500-80-4</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.blavatskyfoundation.org/carrith1.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.blavatskyfoundation.org/carrith1.htm" rel="nofollow">Critique of Williams' book by Walter A. Carrithers, Jr</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBleiler2009"><a href="/wiki/Everett_F._Bleiler" title="Everett F. Bleiler">Bleiler, Everett</a> (1948). <i>The Checklist of Fantastic Literature</i>. Chicago: Shasta Publishers. pp.&#160;54.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Checklist+of+Fantastic+Literature&amp;rft.aulast=Bleiler&amp;rft.aufirst=Everett&amp;rft.au=Bleiler%2C+Everett&amp;rft.date=1948&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B54&amp;rft.place=Chicago&amp;rft.pub=Shasta+Publishers&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Madame_Blavatsky"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
